courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students will be able to:

* integrate and illustrate understanding: through learning how biotechnology, entrepreneurship and healthcare management intersect, illustrates activities and considerations essential to building a successful business or management strategy;
* conduct critical analysis: develop skills to evaluate biotech and healthcare models and policies;
* learn research and independent study skills: gain experience in independent research and data analysis;
* apply knowledge: to analyze business models or polices related to biotech, entrepreneurship, and healthcare management.
* discuss from an entrepreneurial perspective: foster innovation and growth by critically evaluating existing models and policies.
